{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10a2e032-917f-4535-9f38-d274a55fc4f6","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2. Here's the modern recommended pattern:\n\n**Constructor injection for `TestContext`** (preferred over the legacy static property):\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext injection via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async per-class init (runs once)\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassSetupAsync(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // async one-time setup here\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — use for sync setup and `TestContext` injection (MSTest v3+).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — use for async per-test setup (`async Task`).\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — use for async one-time class setup (must be `static`).\n- Avoid the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern — constructor injection is the modern approach.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10eb6381-2a3b-4ae9-b512-ebcd1a569755","outputTokens":332,"requestId":"1BC3:19BA48:216C76E:251BF14:6A03D72F"},"id":"4e41568b-b46e-4a5c-b78d-3a29fd13cb40","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:43:19.058Z","parentId":"73c7de02-4b0a-42e9-831d-8b427fdad77d"}
